==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|misheren|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|mishȳran}}, {{m|ang|mishīeran||to hear amiss, not listen to, disobey}}, equivalent to {{prefix|mis|hear}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/mɪsˈhɪə(ɹ)/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪə(ɹ)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|mishears|mishearing|misheard}}

# To [[hear]] [[wrongly]].
# To [[misunderstand]].

